<item>
            <title>[MATH-938] Line.revert() is imprecise</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-938</link>
                <project id="12310485" key="MATH">Commons Math</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Line.revert() only maintains ~10 digits for the direction. This becomes an issue when the line&apos;s position is evaluated far from the origin. A simple fix would be to use Vector3D.negate() for the direction.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, is there a reason why Line is not immutable? It is just comprised of two vectors.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
